  <h2><strong>What are LMPA?</strong></h2>
  <p>LMPA&trade; are <strong>Low Melting Point Alloys</strong> developed by <a href="http://www.interflux.com" target="_blank">Interflux Electronics</a>.</p>
  <p>LMPA-Q&trade; is an <strong>enhanced</strong> LMPA with superior mechanical properties compared to Sn(Ag)Cu alloys (SAC). The most notable difference is that Low Melting Point Alloys are production-optimal between 190&deg;C to 250&deg;C depending on the process where Sn(Ag)Cu is commonly operated between 235&deg;C and 320&deg;C. The benefits are numerous:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>{{#link-to 'locale.speed'}}Solder 5 times faster and with zero defects{{/link-to}}</li>
    <li>{{#link-to 'locale.voiding'}}Reduce solder voiding below 9%{{/link-to}}</li>
    <li>{{#link-to 'locale.costs'}}Lower production costs &amp; increase{{/link-to}}</li>
    <li>{{#link-to 'locale.heat-failures'}}Avoid heat-related board and component failures{{/link-to}}</li>
    <li>{{#link-to 'locale.dross'}}No more dross formation (oxides){{/link-to}}</li>
    <li>{{#link-to 'locale.wetting'}}Achieve excellent wetting{{/link-to}}</li>
  </ul>
  <p>LMPA-Q&trade; can be used for all soldering processes:</p>
  <ul>
   <li>for wave soldering</li>
   <li>for selective soldering</li>
   <li>for reflow soldering</li>
  </ul>
</div>
